.\" ###### Setup ############################################################
.Dd May 11, 2026
.Dt hpct\-node\-removal 1
.Os hpct\-node\-removal
.\" ###### Name #############################################################
.Sh NAME
.Nm hpct\-node\-removal
.Nd Remove a HiPerConTracer Node
.\" ###### Synopsis #########################################################
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm hpct\-node\-removal NODE\_ID
.br
.Op Fl r | Fl Fl remove\-data
.Nm hpct\-node\-removal
.Op Fl h | Fl Fl help
.Nm hpct\-node\-removal
.Op Fl v | Fl Fl version
.\" ###### Description ######################################################
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm hpct\-node\-removal
is the HiPerConTracer node removal script. It is run on the
collector to remove a given node (i.e. delete the corresponding user).
.Pp
.\" ###### Arguments ########################################################
.Sh ARGUMENTS
The following arguments may be provided:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It NODE\_ID
Sets the node ID, a number from 1 to 9999.
.It Fl r | Fl Fl remove\-data
Also remove the data of the node. Default: Keep the data.
.It Fl h | Fl Fl help
Prints command help.
.It Fl v | Fl Fl version
Prints program version.
.El
.\" ###### Exit status ######################################################
.Sh EXIT STATUS
The
.Nm
tool exits with 0 on success, and >0 in case of an error.
.\" ###### Examples #########################################################
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It hpct\-node\-removal 1000
.It hpct\-node\-removal 1
.It hpct\-node\-removal 2 \-\-remove\-data
.It hpct\-node\-removal 3 \-r
.It hpct\-node\-removal \-\-version
.It hpct\-node\-removal \-h
.El
